ocean_s.formula:
z(n,k,j,i) = eta(n,j,i)*(1+s(k)) + depth_c*s(k) + (depth(j,i)-depth_c)*C(k) 
 where 
 C(k)=(1-b)*sinh(a*s(k))/sinh(a) +
           b*(tanh(a*(s(k)+0.5))/(2*tanh(0.5*a)) - 0.5)

time3.long_name: Diurnal cycle: monthly mean of the diurnal cycle (1 hour steps).

p0.long_name: vertical coordinate formula term: reference pressure

depth.long_name: Sea Floor Depth: formula term: thetao

eta.long_name: Sea Surface Height formula term: thetao

phyn.comment: sum of phytoplankton nitrogen component concentrations

difvso.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to prognostic salinity field.

ocontemppadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized eddy advection
ocontemppadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized eddy advection (any form of eddy advection). Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

co3satcalc.long_name: Mole Concentration of Calcite expressed as Carbon in Sea Water at Saturation

dissicnat.comment: Dissolved inorganic carbon (CO3+HCO3+H2CO3) concentration at preindustrial atmospheric xCO2

difmxybo.comment: Lateral biharmonic viscosity applied to the momentum equitions.

phyfe.comment: sum of phytoplankton iron component concentrations

phycalc.long_name: Mole Concentration of Calcareous Phytoplankton expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
phycalc.comment: carbon concentration from calcareous (calcite-producing) phytoplankton component alone

co3satarag.long_name: Mole Concentration of Aragonite expressed as Carbon in Sea Water at Saturation

phypico.long_name: Mole Concentration of Picophytoplankton expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
phypico.comment: carbon concentration from the picophytoplankton (<2 um) component alone

phymisc.long_name: Mole Concentration of Miscellaneous Phytoplankton expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
phymisc.comment: carbon concentration from additional phytoplankton component alone

sf6.long_name: Moles Per Unit Mass of SF6 in Sea Water

opottemppmdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized mesoscale diffusion
opottemppmdiff.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy diffusion. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

zooc.comment: sum of zooplankton carbon component concentrations

chldiaz.long_name: Mass Concentration of Diazotrophs expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water
chldiaz.comment: Chlorophyll concentration from the diazotrophic phytoplankton component alone

bddtdife.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Iron due to Biological Activity
bddtdife.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic iron

bddtdic.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Carbon due to Biological Activity
bddtdic.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic carbon

chlpico.long_name: Mass Concentration of Picophytoplankton expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water
chlpico.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the picophytoplankton (<2 um) component alone

diftrelo.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced diffusive transport oriented along neutral or isopycnal directions. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the neutral diffusivity or isopycnal diffusivity or Redi diffusivity.

dispkexyfo.long_name: ocean kinetic energy dissipation per unit area due to xy friction
dispkexyfo.comment: Depth integrated impacts on kinetic energy arising from lateral frictional dissipation associated with Laplacian and/or biharmonic viscosity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was 3d, whereas the CMIP6 depth integrated diagnostic is sufficient for many purposes and reduces archive requirements.

osaltpadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to parameterized eddy advection
osaltpadvect.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from parameterized eddy advection (any form of eddy advection).

dcalc.comment: Rate of change of Calcite carbon mole concentration  due to dissolution

opottempadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to advection
opottempadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from resolved advection. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

cfc11.long_name: Moles Per Unit Mass of CFC-11 in Sea Water

difvho.comment: Vertical/dianeutral diffusivity applied to prognostic temperature field.

ph.comment: negative log of hydrogen ion concentration with the concentration expressed as mol H kg-1.

bsi.comment: Sum of particulate silica component concentrations

osaltpsmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to parameterized submesoscale advection
osaltpsmadvect.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from parameterized submesoscale eddy advection.

zoomicro.long_name: Mole Concentration of Microzooplankton expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
zoomicro.comment: carbon  concentration from the microzooplankton (<20 um) component alone

bddtdip.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Phosphate due to Biological Activity
bddtdip.comment: Net of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved phosphate

calc.comment: Sum of particulate calcite component concentrations (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

ppdiaz.long_name: Tendency of Mole Concentration of Organic Carbon in Sea Water due to Net Primary Production by Diazotrophs
ppdiaz.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by the diazotrophic phytoplankton component alone

bacc.comment: Sum of bacterial carbon component concentrations

diftrblo.long_name: ocean tracer diffusivity due to parameterized mesoscale advection
diftrblo.comment: Ocean tracer diffusivity associated with parameterized eddy-induced advective transport. Sometimes this diffusivity is called the 'thickness' diffusivity. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was called 'ocean tracer bolus laplacian diffusivity'.  The CMIP6 name is physically more relevant.

phydiaz.long_name: Mole Concentration of Diazotrophs Expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
phydiaz.comment: carbon concentration from the diazotrophic phytoplankton component alone

opottemppmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized mesoscale advection
opottemppmadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy advection. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

arag.comment: Sum of particulate aragonite components (e.g. Phytoplankton, Detrital, etc.)

physi.comment: sum of phytoplankton silica component concentrations

osalttend.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content
osalttend.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from all processes.

ppmisc.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by other phytoplankton components alone

pppico.long_name: Tendency of Mole Concentration of Organic Carbon in Sea Water due to Net Primary Production by Picophytoplankton
pppico.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by the picophytoplankton (<2 um) component alone

phydiat.long_name: Mole Concentration of Diatoms expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
phydiat.comment: carbon from the diatom phytoplankton component concentration alone

chl.comment: Sum of chlorophyll from all phytoplankton group concentrations.  In most models this is equal to chldiat+chlmisc, that is the sum of Diatom Chlorophyll Mass Concentration and Other Phytoplankton Chlorophyll Mass Concentration

pnitrate.long_name: Primary Carbon Production by Phytoplankton due to Nitrate Uptake Alone
pnitrate.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by phytoplankton due to nitrate uptake alone

tnpeo.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
tnpeo.long_name: tendency of ocean potential energy content
tnpeo.comment: Rate that work is done against vertical stratification, as measured by the vertical heat and salt diffusivity. Report here as depth integrated two-dimensional field.

co3.long_name: Mole Concentration of Carbonate expressed as Carbon in Sea Water

pop.comment: sum of particulate organic phosphorus component concentrations

opottempdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized dianeutral mixing
opottempdiff.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized dianeutral mixing. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

ocontempdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized dianeutral mixing
ocontempdiff.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized dianeutral mixing. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

pon.comment: sum of particulate organic nitrogen component concentrations

chlmisc.comment: Chlorophyll from additional phytoplankton component concentrations alone

cfc12.long_name: Moles Per Unit Mass of CFC-12 in Sea Water

bddtdisi.long_name: Rate of Change of Dissolved Inorganic Silicate due to Biological Activity
bddtdisi.comment: Net of biological terms in time rate of change of dissolved inorganic silicate

opottemppadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized eddy advection
opottemppadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized eddy advection (any form of eddy advection). Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

ocontempadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to advection
ocontempadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from resolved advection. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

chlcalc.long_name: Mass Concentration of Calcareous Phytoplankton expressed as Chlorophyll in Sea Water
chlcalc.comment: chlorophyll concentration from the calcite-producing phytoplankton component alone

detoc.comment: Sum of detrital organic carbon component concentrations

pp.comment: total primary (organic carbon) production by phytoplankton

darag.comment: Rate of change of Aragonite carbon mole concentration  due to dissolution

osaltdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to parameterized dianeutral mixing
osaltdiff.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from parameterized dianeutral mixing.

bddtdin.long_name: Rate of Change of Nitrogen Nutrient due to Biological Activity
bddtdin.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of nitrogen nutrients (e.g. NO3+NH4)

ppdiat.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by the diatom component alone

fescav.comment: Dissolved Fe removed through nonbiogenic scavenging onto particles

osaltpmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to parameterized mesoscale advection
osaltpmadvect.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy advection.

fediss.comment: Dissolution, remineralization and desorption of iron back to the dissolved phase

talk.comment: total alkalinity equivalent concentration (including carbonate, nitrogen, silicate, and borate components)

ocontemppsmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized submesoscale advection
ocontemppsmadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized submesoscale eddy advection. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

bddtalk.long_name: Rate of Change of Alkalinity due to Biological Activity
bddtalk.comment: Net total of biological terms in time rate of change of alkalinity

ocontemptend.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content
ocontemptend.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from all processes. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

opottemptend.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content
opottemptend.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from all processes. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

chldiat.comment: Chlorophyll from diatom phytoplankton component concentration alone

bfe.comment: Sum of particulate organic iron component concentrations

talknat.comment: total alkalinity equivalent concentration (including carbonate, borate, phosphorus, silicon, and nitrogen components) at preindustrial atmospheric xCO2

zoomeso.long_name: Mole Concentration of Mesozooplankton expressed as Carbon in Sea Water
zoomeso.comment: carbon  concentration from mesozooplankton (20-200 um) component alone

ppcalc.long_name: Tendency of Mole Concentration of Organic Carbon in Sea Water due to Net Primary Production by Calcareous Phytoplankton
ppcalc.comment: Primary (organic carbon) production by the calcite-producing phytoplankton component alone

dfe.comment: Dissolved iron in sea water,  including both Fe2+ and Fe3+ ions (but not particulate detrital iron)

expc.comment: Downward flux of particulate organic carbon

phyc.comment: sum of phytoplankton carbon component concentrations.  In most (all?) cases this is the sum of phycdiat and phycmisc (i.e., 'Diatom Carbon Concentration' and 'Non-Diatom Phytoplankton Carbon Concentration'

opottemppsmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water potential temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized submesoscale advection
opottemppsmadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized submesoscale eddy advection. Reported only for models that use potential temperature as prognostic field.

dissoc.comment: Sum of dissolved carbon component concentrations explicitly represented (i.e. not ~40 uM refractory unless explicit)

zoocmisc.comment: carbon from additional zooplankton component concentrations alone (e.g. Micro, meso).  Since the models all have different numbers of components, this variable has been included to provide a check for intercomparison between models since some phytoplankton groups are supersets.

tnkebto.long_name: tendency of ocean eddy kinetic energy content due to parameterized eddy advection
tnkebto.comment: Depth integrated impacts on kinetic energy arising from parameterized eddy-induced advection. For CMIP5, this diagnostic was 3d, whereas the CMIP6 depth integrated diagnostic is sufficient for many purposes and reduces archive requirements.

osaltpmdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to parameterized mesoscale diffusion
osaltpmdiff.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy diffusion.

graz.long_name: Total Grazing of Phytoplankton by Zooplankton

ocontemppmdiff.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized mesoscale diffusion
ocontemppmdiff.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy diffusion. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.

osaltadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water salinity expressed as salt content due to advection
osaltadvect.comment: Tendency of salt content for a grid cell from resolved advection.

difmxylo.comment: Lateral Laplacian viscosity applied to the momentum equitions.

ocontemppmadvect.long_name: tendency of sea water conservative temperature expressed as heat content due to parameterized mesoscale advection
ocontemppmadvect.comment: Tendency of heat content for a grid cell from parameterized mesoscale eddy advection. Reported only for models that use conservative temperature as prognostic field.
